-- Abengoa Signs Final Accord on Waste-Unit Sale to Focus on Water
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-06-14T10:52:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-14/abengoa-signs-final-accord-on-waste-unit-sale-to-focus-on-water.html
Abengoa SA (ABG) , a solar-thermal power
and water desalination plant developer, said it signed a final
agreement for the sale of its Befesa industrial waste unit,
allowing it to focus on its water and solar businesses.  The sale to Triton Partners funds amounts to 620 million
euros ($826 million) after debt, was announced on April 18 and
is to be completed next month, according to a statement today
from Seville, Spain-based Abengoa. Befesa manages industrial-waste plants in Europe, Asia and  South America .  Abengoa, which has developed desalination plants from
Algeria to India, is also building a second-generation biofuel
plant in Kansas, saying startup is expected early next year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
